 Hi Everyone.<br>
 I'm Izumien, level 20 wizard on Fennin Ro. I've been doing the Staff of the Wheel quest for a couple days now. In the bag are rods from Erud's, Qeynos Aqua, Rathe, Oasis, Unrest, Dargor's, Neriak, and Highpass. I died twice in Rathe, but the rest have been clean so far. I still have to do Everfrost, but I figure I'll leave that one to the end, so I'm right there to finish up the quest.<br>
 Anyways, on to my troubles. Lower Guk is a total maze. I've gotten maps, but they are still quite hard to read. Also, Invis to Undead and regular invis don't stack, and I have the wrong one at the wrong time. I had regular invis to go by some killer bats when an undead frog attacked. I was only 1 bubble into level 20 when I started, and now I'm one death from 19 and no self TPs. I camped at a zone point between Upper Guk and Lower Guk, and don't know whether to call it quits and port out, or keep trying.<br>
 Seems like Guk is pretty empty now that Kunark and Velious are out, so there are a ton of wandering mobs.<br>
 Any suggestions?<br>
<br>
 Izumien<br>
 Level 20-19-20-19-20 wizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagatone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magatone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/17/00 5:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rod in Guk *sigh*</span><hr size=1> If you go down the left tunnel in the bedroom and hug the left wall through the bat room they won't agro to you, even if you don't have invis up.  Get past the first two live frog spawns at the top of lower guk, then get ITU and make a mad dash for the hand room.  From there, it's a whole different ballgame as to how you get the rod.  The easiest way is to wait for it to be camped.  That failing, have something like the shiny brass idol on you and be prepaired to die.  Make sure you avoid the pitfall trap right outside the handroom though.  Falling through that will almost guarentee agroing something (it did in my case anyway).  Good luck!<br>
<br>
P.S.  I got my staff of the wheel at lvl 18, so it can be done!  Don't give up hope! <p>Magatone Brac'Taur<BR>
Wizard of the 48th rank<BR>
Ambassador of Merchants of Honour<BR>
