 I've come up with a plan.<br>
 I'll stay bound at the Lguk zone for now, but travel to Highpass Hold. There, I shall gain most of level 20 in buffer exp, and try to get my hands on a Shiny Brass Idol. Barring that, I'll make some money to buy a couple IVU potions.<br>
 I was thinking of a plan once I got to the hand room. What if I bound outside it, and TPed to Lfay. There, I'd get a SoW, and another IVU potion. Gate back to the Hand room, agro the hand, and lead it on a wild goose chase through Lower Guk. I'd either die or zone, probably, die, but appear next to an empty hand room. Waltz in, grab the rod, and TP back to Lfay with rod #9. Sound ok?<br>
 <br>
 Izumien <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/17/00 1:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A couple Ideas. . .</span><hr size=1> I don't think you would get the hand far enough away for that to work. I think you are inviting a bind-death loop that will be very painful.  <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulindyile.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lindyile</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/00 1:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A couple Ideas. . .</span><hr size=1> When I got my staff I asked the people in the lord room to pull the hand for me.  When they pulled I darted for the rod and gated out.  All I needed was invis vs. undead for this to work.  When you get to the room you should no longer need it as they clear the way to the room.  Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
