<br>
First and formost, I would like to add in that - &quot;Doing the homework ALWAYS pays off!&quot;<br>
<br>
With that in mind, I'm posting here as, I too just completed the quest.  But with a lesson that I thought I would pass on.  Picture me doing the quest twice!!!  Once for putting the rods in the box and not taking to time to read that it was no drop, the second, for listening to a Troll tell me &quot;I know where that rod is!!! Follow me!&quot;.  We take the underwater tavern, I get to the other side, see the rod on the floor, and even give the Trollie a GG for his help!  Imagine my horror when I attempted to combine the rods only to see:<br>
<br>
 &quot;The items in this quantity could not be combined to produce anything!!&quot;<br>
<br>
I think I soiled myself..  Multiple times..<br>
<br>
After wiping away the tears, I decide to actually read and do an identify on each and every rod the next time.  Sure enough, the&quot;rod&quot; that the troll led me to was actually a &quot;Sceptre&quot;!!!  <br>
<br>
So, after destroying that poop stick, I decide to send out some shouts about the Animated hand room.  Some one leads me to the safe &quot;hallway&quot; before you corner to get to the prisons, pits, etc, and I wait.  Then invis drops!!  So I wait, and wait, and wait, and..<br>
<br>
Finally, a &quot;lord&quot; group takes the room and with me at this point so desperate to get this staff just out of principle standing there with no ITU, I bind.  Well after the puller brought the hand to my spot(still haven't decided whether it was intentional or not).  One of them gave a shout that the hand was gone(no S&amp;*T!) and that I should do so and get out of there.<br>
<br>
In any case, the moral of this story is as follows.<br>
<br>
ITU POTIONS will save you so much time on this quest.  Just spend the cash and get a few of them.  Depending on someone to cast ITU on you could prove to be a very frustrating as well as deadly process.  Also, paying for guides in GUK(depending upon your level - and if you have the cash), never hurts.<br>
<br>
Suenydar of Mith Marr.<br>
<br>
