 After all the great responses to this forum, I'd like to thank everyone for their advice.<br>
 I succeeded in getting my rod from Guk today! <br>
 After an unsuccessful Quad-Kiting attempt with Crag Spiders in East Karana, I appeared naked at my bind point in Lower Guk. I had gotten about a bubble of exp into 20, so wasn't in any danger of losing my TPs with one death. So, I shout, is AM camped? And sure enough, it is. I explain my situation to the group leader in tells, and he agrees to pull the hand.<br>
 I had used all 3 of my IVU potions before this, learning the route off by heart. I grabbed an IVU from a nearby enchanter, and make my way through guk. I found the hand room for the 1st time! The mighty AM group charges up behind me, and attacks the hand! Just then, my IVU fails, and the Hand starts attacking me. I get Force Shocked and the like, but the hand is pulled off. Gasping, at under one bubble of life, I swim up to the surface, grab the rob, and gate away safely, rod in inventory.<br>
 Thus ends my adventures in Lower Guk, at least for now. Only Everfrost remains, and I left that to last because the quest starts right there, too. <br>
 Hopefully next time I post, it's with a Staff of the Wheel in my hands!<br>
<br>
 Izumien<br>
 Holder of the 9 rods! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucaladari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/20/00 1:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Got it!</span><hr size=1> <br>
